{
  "bead_id": "B-568b332e",
  "title": "Improve takt init output with colors and visual polish",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "The 'takt init' command currently outputs plain text lines like:\n  '  Created .takt/ directories'\n  '  Wrote .takt/config.yaml'\n  '  Done. Run takt summary to verify the setup.'\n\nMake the output visually polished using ANSI colors and symbols. The project already has a ConsoleReporter in src/agent_takt/console.py with color/symbol helpers \u2014 use those rather than raw ANSI codes.\n\nDesired style (approximate):\n- Each completed step uses a green checkmark (\u2713) prefix, e.g. '  \u2713 Created .takt/ directories'\n- The section header '=== takt init ===' could be bold or cyan\n- The final 'Done.' line should be bold green\n- Any warning or skipped-step lines use yellow\n- Keep it readable in non-TTY environments (no color if not a TTY, consistent with how ConsoleReporter already handles it)\n\nFiles to modify: src/agent_takt/onboarding.py, and possibly src/agent_takt/cli.py where init output is printed.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- 'takt init' on a TTY shows colored output with checkmark prefixes on each step.\n- 'takt init' piped to a file (non-TTY) degrades gracefully \u2014 no raw escape codes in the output.\n- All existing tests pass.",
